# AddressSanitizer suppressions for the sanitized latte-dock build
# (docs/ub-catching-plan.md, Prong A). Referenced by both launchers via
# ASAN_OPTIONS=suppressions=... (scripts/run-asan-dock.sh nested,
# scripts/start-dock-sanitized.sh live).
#
# STARTS EMPTY ON PURPOSE. A suppression hides a finding, so an over-broad
# entry here re-creates exactly the silent-UB failure this whole initiative
# exists to end (CLAUDE.md "never silently swallow a failure"). Add an entry
# ONLY for a report you have traced into uninstrumented system code
# (Qt/KF6/Plasma/glib) and confirmed is not our bug - never to quiet our own
# code.
#
# ASan's suppression file only covers a FEW categories - interceptor-based
# reports and ODR violations, NOT heap/stack-buffer-overflow or
# use-after-free (those are always fatal, which is what we want for our code).
# Supported forms:
#   interceptor_via_fun:<mangled_or_demangled_function_name>
#   interceptor_via_lib:<substring_of_library_path>   e.g. libglib-2.0.so
#   odr_violation:<global_symbol_name>
#
# Leaks are handled by detect_leaks=0 in the launchers (Qt/Plasma leak at exit
# by design; leak spam would drown the UB signal), so no leak: entries here.
#
# Example (commented - uncomment and narrow to the real library if a
# library-internal interceptor report ever buries the live run):
# interceptor_via_lib:libfontconfig.so
